Subject: Re: [T2] Compression Test Results

On Friday, August 13, 2004, at 05:12PM, Michael Knight <vwdormer(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

>I just finished doing a compression test on the engine in question, here are 
>the results:
>
>Cyl. #     I      II      III       IV
>
>Test1   94     143   122     125
>Test2   90     144   117     121
>Test3   91     145   115     120
>Test4   92     145   116     119

II is high, III and IV look normal for age, and I is heading south for rebuild country.

>Now I know that they all should be over 100 PSI and within 15% of each 
>other. Is that 15% of the average of all of them?

15% is so the engine remains in a better state of balance. You are looking at 15% difference between the highest and lowest readings to minimize bottom end wear (as much as you can with an unbalanced VW engine). You've got 38% but you'll recover if you can fix #1.

>Am I just looking at this wrong? If this is correct then I guess I better 
>start planning the tear down and rebuild. Any suggestions or comments?

Buses with worse results are still driving down the road but you've got a head replacement in your future.

